Iteration: 1 - register with sol
Request Description
### Register with SOL This endpoint allows you to register a component with SOL by making an HTTP POST. #### Request Body - `star`: STAR-UUID of the star. - `sol`: COM-UUID of SOL. - `component`: COM-UUID of the registering component. - `com-ip`: IP address of the registering component. - `com-tcp`: PORT at the registering component for the tcp connection. - `status`: STATUS of the register process. Default: 200. #### Response The response format is `text/plain` with the following possible response codes: - 200: OK - 401: Unauthorized: mismatching information about the star - 403: No room left | Forbidden: Star is full - 409: Conflict: mismatching information about the registering component The response text itself is always empty.

Iteration: 1 - get component status
Request Description
### GET component status This endpoint allows SOL to check on a component, whether it is still active and functioning. #### Path variables - `COM-UUID`: COM-UUID of the component to check on. #### Request parameters - `star`: STAR-UUID of the star. #### Response The response format is `application/json` with the following possible response codes: - 200: OK: Component active and part of the requested star - 401: Unauthorized: Component not part of the requested star OR empty COM-UUID - 409: Conflict: mismatching COM-UUID If the response code is not 200, the response body is empty. Else, the response body consists of the following key-value-pairs: - `star`: STAR-UUID of the star. - `sol`: COM-UUID of SOL. - `component`: COM-UUID of the registering component. - `com-ip`: IP address of the checked component. - `com-tcp`: PORT of the checked component. - `status`: STATUS of the checked component.

Iteration: 1 - unregister component
Request Description
### DELETE component from star This endpoint allows a component to unregister itself from a star. It can also be used by SOL to remove a specific component. #### Path Variables - `COM-UUID`: COM-UUID of the component to be unregistered. #### Request Parameters - `star`: STAR-UUID of the star. #### Response The response format is `text/plain`, where the text is always empty. If the request is being sent **from a component to SOL**, the following response codes are valid: - `200`: OK: Component successfully removed from the star. - `401`: Unauthorized: Invalid IP of requesting component and/or unknown/wrong STAR-UUID. - `404`: Not Found: Component not known by SOL. If instead the request is being sent from SOL to a component, these responses are valid: - `200`: OK: Component successfully removed from the star. - `401`: Unauthorized: Invalid IP of requesting SOL and/or unknown/wrong STAR-UUID.

Iteration: 11 - unregister component
Request Description
### DELETE component from star This endpoint allows a component to unregister itself from a star. It can also be used by SOL to remove a specific component. #### Path Variables - `COM-UUID`: COM-UUID of the component to be unregistered. #### Request Parameters - `star`: STAR-UUID of the star. #### Response The response format is `text/plain`, where the text is always empty. If the request is being sent **from a component to SOL**, the following response codes are valid: - `200`: OK: Component successfully removed from the star. - `401`: Unauthorized: Invalid IP of requesting component and/or unknown/wrong STAR-UUID. - `404`: Not Found: Component not known by SOL. If instead the request is being sent from SOL to a component, these responses are valid: - `200`: OK: Component successfully removed from the star. - `401`: Unauthorized: Invalid IP of requesting SOL and/or unknown/wrong STAR-UUID.
